The President released a statement on the new national space policy, highlighting America's leadership in space exploration and the technological advancements that have resulted from it. The policy emphasizes peaceful cooperation and collaboration in space, as well as the need to address challenges such as debris and hazards. It also aims to spur a commercial space industry, improve observation of the Earth, and set ambitious goals for NASA in robotic and human space exploration. The policy recognizes the importance of inspiring young people to pursue careers in science and engineering. Overall, it reflects America's commitment to embracing the future and leading the world in space exploration.